    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 169 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Representatives of the British Chiefs of
                        Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25">25 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 880/1</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Agenda for the Next United States–British Staff
                        Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item> The British Chiefs of Staff have now one further item to add to the
                        tentative outline agenda proposed in <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C.
                            S.</gloss> 880.<note n="1" xml:id="d169fn1">
                            <ref target="#d154">Document No. 154</ref>.</note> They suggest that the
                        following item be added: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>(11) Combined Chiefs of Staff Machinery after the war with <persName
                                    corresp="#p_J1">Japan</persName>.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="0326" n="194" xml:id="pg_194"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The British Chiefs of Staff would submit a paper on this item as a basis
                        for discussion.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
